                  <span class="">Page 22 A game is described by its rules, and a better game is produced only by changing the rules. Page 52 Value is relative, truth is not, at least within the realm of ordinary discourse. ... It is not the recognition of fallibility in scientific truths that facilitates man's understanding of his social order and that renders him tolerant of dissent. It is, indeed, the recoggnition of the nec...</span>
